  Locus:
    Page: 464
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Teacher
---
The wise man is always a student. He is ever eager to learn. He never poses
to be a teacher. ... A man of little learning and little understanding is
ever eager to teach. He wants to take up the role of preceptor. He is not
eager to learn.
